{"name": "twpl", "metadata": {"name": "twpl", "version": "0.1.2", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: GNU General Public License v3 (GPLv3)", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Topic :: Software Development", "Topic :: System"], "home_page": "https://github.com/LankyCyril/twpl/", "license": "GPLv3", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["filelock"], "summary": "Two-phase locking via lockfiles", "upload_time": 1733768506}, "documentation": ["### Two-phase locking with lockfiles\n\n- Initial release\n- Currently supports Linux/POSIX only\n- Documentation coming soon\n\nRelies on modifying the number of open file descriptors for a lockfile.\n\nCurrently implements the 2PL lock compatibility table:\n\nLock type  | read-lock | write-lock\n-----------|-----------|-----------\nread-lock  |     Y     |     N\nwrite-lock |     N     |     N\n\nRead locks are called \"concurrent,\" and write locks are called \"exclusive.\"\n\nThe API, the naming, and the implementation are all subjects to change until\nthe first _stable_ release (i.e. until version 1.0.0, or earlier if explicitly\nstated).\n"], "modules": [{"name": "setup", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "setup.get_readme", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "filename", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "setup.meta", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "twpl", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "twpl.__version__", "xref": {"fqname": "twpl.twpl.__version__", "project": null}}, {"name": "twpl.CONCURRENT", "xref": {"fqname": "twpl.twpl.CONCURRENT", "project": null}}, {"name": "twpl.EXCLUSIVE", "xref": {"fqname": "twpl.twpl.EXCLUSIVE", "project": null}}, {"name": "twpl.Twpl", "xref": {"fqname": "twpl.twpl.Twpl", "project": null}}, {"name": "twpl.TwplPlatformError", "xref": {"fqname": "twpl.twpl.TwplPlatformError", "project": null}}, {"name": "twpl.TwplTimeoutError", "xref": {"fqname": "twpl.twpl.TwplTimeoutError", "project": null}}, {"name": "twpl.TwplValueError", "xref": {"fqname": "twpl.twpl.TwplValueError", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "twpl.twpl", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "twpl.twpl.fds_exceed", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "filename", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "mincount", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "fdcache", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Check if number of open file descriptors for `filename`\nexceeds `mincount`"]}, {"name": "twpl.twpl._fds_exceed_posix", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "filename", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "mincount", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "fdcache", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["This replaces fds_exceed. Note that it only checks the number of open\nfds under an acquired FileLock (`Twpl.__acquire_exclusive()`), and the\nnumber of open fds can only grow under the same FileLock as well: via\n`open()` in `Twpl.__acquire_concurrent()`. So while fd symlinks can\ndisappear while we iterate here, there will never be new relevant fds\nmissed by `walk()`."]}], "variables": [{"name": "twpl.twpl.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "twpl.twpl.NamedInt", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "twpl.twpl.TwplPlatformError", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "twpl.twpl.TwplValueError", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "twpl.twpl.TwplTimeoutError", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "twpl.twpl.TwplStateError", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "twpl.twpl._ERR_PROC_TEST", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "twpl.twpl._ERR_PLATFORM_TEST", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "twpl.twpl._ERR_MODE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "twpl.t